transcript.text: Hello everyone, welcome back to the On Print Shop tutorial series.
In one of our previous videos, we learned how to create additional options, assign product options, configure combined pricing, and create the designer rules.
In today's video, we will have an understanding of the option rules and how you can create them to give your customers a unique and tailored shopping experience.
So let's get started.
First go to the Product section of your admin panel.
Then select the product for which you want to create the option Rules.
Click on the Action drop down and select Rules.
Click on the Add button.
Give a name to the rule you are creating such as Rule one.
Select the rule that you want to apply from the drop down.
We have these rules which you can select based on size, quantity where the additional options will be hidden based on the selected size and quantity.
Then there is size additional option where the additional option will be hidden based on the configured size and additional option.
Then we have an additional option where the selected additional option will be hidden based on the selection of configured one additional option.
Next is the size quantity additional option.
Here it will be based on the combination of size, quantity and additional option and with the last rule additional option Base size hide.
You can hide the selected product size based on the selection of configured additional option.
These options vary when you are creating option rules for custom size or dynamic size products.
Here for the size rules instead of size selection, you get the option to select the products area, perimeter, width or height.
Let's create a rule with an additional option based rule type for standard products.
Now from the select option drop down, select Double Sided and from the below additional options, select the Glossy finishing to hide, enable the status as Active and click on Save.
As per the configuration, when the customers select Printing Sides double sided, the glossy option from the finished type should not appear in the drop down.
Let's verify this at the front store as we select double sided from the printing side option.
You can see that in the finish type additional option, there are only two options available, matte and spot UV for selection.
This is how you can create option rules to tailor the product selection offering a smooth buying experience to your customers.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
